2
00:00:15.021 --> 00:00:18.021
[dramatic upbeats plays]

3
00:00:19.812 --> 00:00:24.896
[theme song plays]

4
00:00:49.479 --> 00:00:51.979
[eagle screeching]

5
00:01:42.854 --> 00:01:45.979
[ominous music plays]

6
00:01:48.479 --> 00:01:49.396
Ah!

7
00:01:49.479 --> 00:01:50.646
What is it?!

8
00:01:50.729 --> 00:01:52.271
What does this thing want again?

9
00:01:52.354 --> 00:01:53.604
What is it?

10
00:01:53.687 --> 00:01:55.562
[screams]

11
00:01:56.937 --> 00:01:57.896
What is it?

12
00:01:57.979 --> 00:01:59.646
Tade?

13
00:01:59.729 --> 00:02:00.937
Tade.

14
00:02:01.021 --> 00:02:02.604
Tade!

15
00:02:02.687 --> 00:02:07.354
[wheezing]

16
00:02:08.396 --> 00:02:10.146
-Tade? Tade. what is it?
-[Tade wheezing]

17
00:02:10.229 --> 00:02:12.604
-Tade! Tadetola!
-[wheezing]

18
00:02:12.687 --> 00:02:15.021
-My God! Tade! Ah-ah!
-What happened?

19
00:02:15.104 --> 00:02:16.646
-[Amaka] Tade?
-Leave him.

20
00:02:16.729 --> 00:02:17.729
[Amaka] Eh! Oh!

21
00:02:17.812 --> 00:02:18.937
-[Adedujoye] Leave him.
-It is happening again!

22
00:02:19.021 --> 00:02:20.562
-[Adedunjoye] It's happening again! Tade!
-Tade?!

23
00:02:20.646 --> 00:02:21.687
-Tade?
-Tade!

24
00:02:21.771 --> 00:02:23.354
-Ah!
-Ah! My God!

25
00:02:23.437 --> 00:02:24.979
-I'm in trouble! Tade!
-Let's take him to the Hospital.

26
00:02:25.062 --> 00:02:26.521
-Hospital!
-[Adedunjoye exclaims]

27
00:02:26.604 --> 00:02:27.687
[Amaka] Hospital. Tade!

28
00:02:27.771 --> 00:02:29.437
Tade! I'm finished!

29
00:02:29.521 --> 00:02:30.562
Tadetola!

30
00:02:30.646 --> 00:02:31.812
[suspenseful music plays]

31
00:02:31.896 --> 00:02:33.396
[car hoots]

32
00:02:35.354 --> 00:02:36.354
[tires screeching]

33
00:02:36.437 --> 00:02:38.479
-[Amaka] Nurse!
-[nurse panting]

34
00:02:38.562 --> 00:02:40.687
-Open the door!
-[nurse panting] Ah!

35
00:02:40.771 --> 00:02:43.354
-[Amaka] Hey! Tade! Nurse! Tade!
-[Adedunjoye] Leave him! Leave him to me!

36
00:02:43.437 --> 00:02:45.396
-[Amaka] Nurse! Nurse!
-Leave him! I said leave him!

37
00:02:45.479 --> 00:02:48.187
-I said leave him to me! Leave him!
-[Amaka] Nurse!

38
00:02:48.271 --> 00:02:49.229
[Adedunjoye] Leave him!

39
00:02:49.312 --> 00:02:50.854
-Tade!
-[Adedunjoye] Uh?

40
00:02:50.937 --> 00:02:51.854
-[Amaka] Get out of the way!
-[grunt]

41
00:02:51.937 --> 00:02:53.646
-[panting] Tade!
-Huh?

42
00:02:53.729 --> 00:02:55.104
What has happened?

43
00:02:56.604 --> 00:03:00.104
[tense music plays]

44
00:03:14.396 --> 00:03:17.437
[whooshing sound]

45
00:03:45.896 --> 00:03:47.479
I will not weep over you.

46
00:03:48.312 --> 00:03:50.312
I will not weep over my son.

47
00:03:50.812 --> 00:03:54.271
[sobbing] I will not lose you. Tade.
[sighs heavily]

48
00:03:55.437 --> 00:03:57.229
[tense music plays]

49
00:03:57.896 --> 00:03:59.229
[sniffs] Uh?

50
00:04:00.021 --> 00:04:02.854
[tense music crescendos]

51
00:04:20.854 --> 00:04:22.312
-How did you know?
-[Priests] Ah.

52
00:04:22.396 --> 00:04:23.687
-[heaving]
-Ah Your Highness.

53
00:04:24.396 --> 00:04:25.687
-There's no way something like this
-[heaving]

54
00:04:25.771 --> 00:04:27.979
could happen without me knowing about it.

55
00:04:28.062 --> 00:04:29.104
Yes.

56
00:04:29.187 --> 00:04:30.979
Look. your son's case
is not a hospital issue.

57
00:04:31.062 --> 00:04:32.729
I didn't want to say it
in the Queen's presence.

58
00:04:32.812 --> 00:04:34.271
-that's why I called you out.
-[huffs]

59
00:04:34.354 --> 00:04:36.187
If he completes the circle…

60
00:04:36.271 --> 00:04:37.104
[huffs]

61
00:04:37.187 --> 00:04:39.021
Priest. he was going from one circle

62
00:04:39.104 --> 00:04:40.354
of life to another. that was the dream

63
00:04:40.437 --> 00:04:42.604
I was having before you woke me. [inhales]

64
00:04:42.687 --> 00:04:43.979
[panting] Priest. help… help me.

65
00:04:44.062 --> 00:04:46.271
-Your Highness. I know.
-[grunts]

66
00:04:46.354 --> 00:04:47.521
-That's why I'm here.
-[grunts]

67
00:04:47.604 --> 00:04:50.187
There's no way I won't know
about all that is going on.

68
00:04:50.271 --> 00:04:54.646
Look. let's leave all questions
till after we've taken care of the boy.

69
00:04:54.729 --> 00:04:55.812
Quickly!

70
00:04:56.312 --> 00:04:57.146
You mean we should take him out

71
00:04:57.229 --> 00:04:58.521
-of the hospital?
-He must leave this place!

72
00:04:58.604 --> 00:04:59.812
-Right now!
-Right now?

73
00:04:59.896 --> 00:05:01.521
Yes! Right now!

74
00:05:01.604 --> 00:05:04.646
[troubled music plays]

75
00:05:09.646 --> 00:05:12.271
[whooshing sound]

76
00:05:17.687 --> 00:05:20.771
[men in Yoruba] ♪ The head of a pigeon ♪

77
00:05:21.937 --> 00:05:24.437
♪ The tail of a pigeon ♪

78
00:05:25.187 --> 00:05:32.104
♪ The wings of a pigeon
Perform your duties ♪

79
00:05:32.729 --> 00:05:36.437
♪ Doors open and close ♪

80
00:05:36.521 --> 00:05:40.396
♪ Seasons come and go ♪

81
00:05:40.479 --> 00:05:43.396
♪ The head of a pigeon… ♪

82
00:05:58.437 --> 00:06:00.646
[Priest] The one who
sees death and fears not.

83
00:06:04.229 --> 00:06:06.854
The one who sees diseases and fears not.
[tense music plays]

84
00:06:09.146 --> 00:06:12.646
The shaker! The one
who shakes the entire town.

85
00:06:13.521 --> 00:06:14.479
[Adedunjoye]Tade.

86
00:06:14.562 --> 00:06:16.187
You sent for Tadetola…

87
00:06:18.271 --> 00:06:20.146
you asked him to come to heaven.

88
00:06:22.437 --> 00:06:24.729
Tadetola refuses.

89
00:06:24.812 --> 00:06:27.771
He says he won't respond
to the call of heaven.

90
00:06:29.062 --> 00:06:30.812
You who locks doors.

91
00:06:32.896 --> 00:06:35.312
Go help Tadetola lock heaven's door.

92
00:06:38.729 --> 00:06:40.937
You who opens the worlds…

93
00:06:43.396 --> 00:06:45.271
Now open the door of life.

94
00:06:47.604 --> 00:06:49.854
Open the door of life for Tadetola.

95
00:06:51.729 --> 00:06:54.062
Tadetola has sent a white piece of cloth.

96
00:06:54.146 --> 00:06:56.271
he said he's not responding
to heaven's call.

97
00:06:56.354 --> 00:06:58.146
Tadetola!

98
00:06:58.229 --> 00:07:01.104
You must respond to the call
of life. not the call of heaven.

99
00:07:02.271 --> 00:07:04.812
Open the door of life. you gatekeeper.

100
00:07:05.396 --> 00:07:07.229
Tadetola!

101
00:07:07.729 --> 00:07:09.271
[Tade sneezes]

102
00:07:10.354 --> 00:07:11.479
[sneezes]

103
00:07:11.562 --> 00:07:12.687
-That's good.
-Tade!

104
00:07:12.771 --> 00:07:13.854
-Tade!
-[Tade sneezes]

105
00:07:13.937 --> 00:07:14.812
-[Priest] That's good.
-Tade!

106
00:07:14.896 --> 00:07:16.437
-Leave him!
-[Tade sneezes]

107
00:07:16.521 --> 00:07:17.479
-Well done.
-[Adedunjoye] Tade!

108
00:07:17.562 --> 00:07:19.104
-[Amaka pants]
-[Adedunjoye] Tade!

109
00:07:19.187 --> 00:07:20.812
-Thank you God.
-[Amaka] Tade!

110
00:07:20.896 --> 00:07:22.271
[Adedunjoye] Thank you God.

111
00:07:23.104 --> 00:07:24.562
[Priest] Evil has been averted.

112
00:07:25.271 --> 00:07:28.062
The one who isn't powerful
enough is acting powerful.

113
00:07:28.896 --> 00:07:32.229
You should know that you
ought to have stayed in your league.

114
00:07:32.312 --> 00:07:34.021
A divination for Orunmila was given

115
00:07:34.979 --> 00:07:36.729
when the witches fought with him.

116
00:07:37.312 --> 00:07:41.312
He said both
the young witches and old witches

117
00:07:41.396 --> 00:07:43.146
he would conquer them all.

118
00:07:49.729 --> 00:07:51.104
Your Highness.

119
00:07:51.687 --> 00:07:53.229
[Adedunjoye] Am I at fault?

120
00:07:54.979 --> 00:07:58.021
Is it…Is it a sin
to come and serve your town?

121
00:07:59.604 --> 00:08:01.104
Or…[grunts]

122
00:08:01.187 --> 00:08:04.937
is it because I took the title of the
Onilara to make Ilara a better place?

123
00:08:05.479 --> 00:08:08.646
[huffs] What exactly is my offence?
Please tell me. Priest.

124
00:08:08.729 --> 00:08:09.812
What is my offence?

125
00:08:09.896 --> 00:08:11.479
-Your Highness.
-[panting]

126
00:08:11.562 --> 00:08:13.062
Your offence is that

127
00:08:13.146 --> 00:08:14.771
you didn't do what Ifa asked you to do.

128
00:08:14.854 --> 00:08:16.937
-Ah-ah! [panting]
-Look.

129
00:08:17.021 --> 00:08:19.521
this is just the tip of the iceberg.

130
00:08:19.604 --> 00:08:21.896
If we continue to thread on this path.

131
00:08:21.979 --> 00:08:23.104
the end result.

132
00:08:23.646 --> 00:08:25.687
-will affect everyone in the land.
-Ah!

133
00:08:26.562 --> 00:08:30.146
Hear this. Tadetola
has not completely escaped death.

134
00:08:30.229 --> 00:08:31.562
-Huh?
-[tensed tune plays]

135
00:08:31.646 --> 00:08:33.771
We just saved him temporarily.

136
00:08:33.854 --> 00:08:35.479
[suspenseful music plays]

137
00:08:35.562 --> 00:08:36.396
My Tadetola?

138
00:08:36.479 --> 00:08:40.437
-Yes.
-Ah!

139
00:08:40.521 --> 00:08:42.229
-What is it?
-[grunts]

140
00:08:42.312 --> 00:08:45.021
-[sobs] God.
-[wistful music plays]

141
00:08:45.104 --> 00:08:47.187
what is it? [panting]

142
00:08:47.271 --> 00:08:48.521
What is it?

143
00:08:49.146 --> 00:08:50.937
The father ate the forbidden fruit.

144
00:08:51.937 --> 00:08:54.104
the grandson is the one bearing the brunt.

145
00:08:55.354 --> 00:08:58.396
What have I done
to deserve all this? [sobs]

146
00:08:59.104 --> 00:09:01.646
Please have mercy on me. Ah!

147
00:09:02.479 --> 00:09:03.937
I should marry them?

148
00:09:04.021 --> 00:09:06.729
[whimpers] And I'm
to love them wholeheartedly.

149
00:09:06.812 --> 00:09:08.354
At least you know where I'm from.

150
00:09:08.437 --> 00:09:09.729
you know where I came from.

151
00:09:09.812 --> 00:09:11.437
I have my own way of doing things.

152
00:09:11.521 --> 00:09:13.687
I had something I was doing before this!

153
00:09:13.771 --> 00:09:15.104
What is it?!

154
00:09:15.646 --> 00:09:16.479
Ah!

155
00:09:16.562 --> 00:09:17.771
-Your Highness.
-[gulps. sobs]

156
00:09:17.854 --> 00:09:19.104
-[huffs]
-You have to marry them

157
00:09:19.187 --> 00:09:20.687
one after the other.

158
00:09:21.646 --> 00:09:24.437
That's what will serve
as your deliverance.

159
00:09:25.187 --> 00:09:29.562
and that of others that will become
the Onilara in Adejuwon's family.

160
00:09:30.062 --> 00:09:31.937
-Priest [huffs]
-Hm?

161
00:09:33.062 --> 00:09:36.021
[sighs] Why do I have to be
the one who gets punished?

162
00:09:38.562 --> 00:09:39.521
It's not fair.

163
00:09:40.062 --> 00:09:41.562
Priest. it's not fair. [inhales deeply]

164
00:09:41.646 --> 00:09:44.646
I haven't committed any sin.
I didn't offend anyone. [heaving]

165
00:09:44.729 --> 00:09:46.354
-[wistful music continues]
-Why does it have to be me?

166
00:09:46.437 --> 00:09:49.021
Why does… I came
to Ilara with a pure heart.

167
00:09:49.687 --> 00:09:51.271
My daughter Fola is dead.

168
00:09:51.354 --> 00:09:53.396
Tadetola is not completely saved.

169
00:09:53.479 --> 00:09:55.437
What did I do to deserve this? [heaving]

170
00:09:55.521 --> 00:09:57.896
What is my offence? Priest. [sobs]

171
00:09:57.979 --> 00:10:00.229
What is my offence?

172
00:10:00.312 --> 00:10:06.187
What is my… [panting]

173
00:10:08.937 --> 00:10:11.812
[birds chirping]

174
00:10:22.854 --> 00:10:24.229
[door closes]

175
00:10:27.062 --> 00:10:29.229
[birds chirping]

176
00:10:34.187 --> 00:10:38.229
[ancient melodies play]

177
00:11:08.729 --> 00:11:15.229
[ancient melodies play]

178
00:11:23.646 --> 00:11:25.604
Your Highness. [grunts]

179
00:11:43.312 --> 00:11:48.229
[ancient melodies playing]

180
00:12:04.396 --> 00:12:05.979
[Queen clears her throat]

181
00:12:06.979 --> 00:12:09.437
[all] Your Highness.

182
00:12:10.521 --> 00:12:12.021
[Adedunjoye] Thank you. I'm grateful.

183
00:12:12.562 --> 00:12:14.104
-It shall be well with you.
-[all] So shall it be.

184
00:12:14.604 --> 00:12:15.521
You'll all bear children.

185
00:12:15.604 --> 00:12:17.729
-[all] So shall it be.
-You'll not make mistakes.

186
00:12:17.812 --> 00:12:18.812
So shall it be.

187
00:12:18.896 --> 00:12:20.562
-You'll not speak in error.
-So shall it be.

188
00:12:20.646 --> 00:12:22.729
May true love be established

189
00:12:22.812 --> 00:12:25.854
-in our hearts forever and ever.
-So shall it be.

190
00:12:25.937 --> 00:12:26.979
Rise up.

191
00:12:27.729 --> 00:12:29.021
[all] Thank you. Your Highness.

192
00:12:30.312 --> 00:12:31.729
[Queen in blue] Your Highness.

193
00:12:32.229 --> 00:12:33.312
[Queen in glasses] Hm!

194
00:12:33.854 --> 00:12:35.979
-Your Highness.
-Our husband.

195
00:12:36.062 --> 00:12:37.729
-[Queen 1 chuckles]
-[Adedunjoye] Thank you.

196
00:12:38.604 --> 00:12:39.812
I'll see you in the bedroom.

197
00:12:39.896 --> 00:12:42.479
Go to your rooms
I'll come to you one after the other.

198
00:12:43.021 --> 00:12:44.687
[all] Your Highness.

199
00:12:44.771 --> 00:12:46.521
-[Queen 2] Your Highness.
-[all chuckle]

200
00:12:46.604 --> 00:12:48.312
[Queen 2] Well done.

201
00:12:49.396 --> 00:12:51.271
[all chuckle] Your Highness.

202
00:12:51.354 --> 00:12:53.979
[laughs]

203
00:12:57.646 --> 00:12:59.062
[Queen 5] Your Highness.

204
00:13:00.354 --> 00:13:01.729
Our husband.

205
00:13:05.479 --> 00:13:07.312
-Have you forgiven us?
-Hmm.

206
00:13:09.646 --> 00:13:11.062
Thank you.

207
00:13:11.562 --> 00:13:12.979
By God's grace.

208
00:13:13.979 --> 00:13:15.812
your reign will bring peace
to the whole town.

209
00:13:15.896 --> 00:13:17.021
So shall it be.

210
00:13:17.729 --> 00:13:18.979
-So shall it be.
-[pants]

211
00:13:19.062 --> 00:13:20.687
-That's what I desire.
-[huffs]

212
00:13:21.729 --> 00:13:22.562
Ah!

213
00:13:22.646 --> 00:13:24.854
[ecstatic music playing]

214
00:13:28.646 --> 00:13:30.604
[singer in Yoruba] ♪ Hail hail ♪

215
00:13:33.562 --> 00:13:35.646
♪ Husband of dark and fair women ♪

216
00:13:36.229 --> 00:13:38.271
♪ Husband to women of substance ♪

217
00:13:38.354 --> 00:13:40.771
♪ Son of King Adekogbe ♪

218
00:13:40.854 --> 00:13:44.812
[vocalists] ♪ Keep reigning ♪

219
00:13:44.896 --> 00:13:46.354
[singer] ♪ I said ♪

220
00:13:46.437 --> 00:13:49.021
[vocalists] ♪ Keep reigning ♪

221
00:13:49.104 --> 00:13:52.729
♪ All the wives
Have asked me to greet you ♪

222
00:13:56.562 --> 00:13:58.562
♪ Keep reigning ♪

223
00:14:04.229 --> 00:14:06.062
[singer] ♪ The Onilara
Is doing something great ♪

224
00:14:06.146 --> 00:14:08.437
♪ Give me room to do mine ♪

225
00:14:08.937 --> 00:14:13.646
♪ May this time
The peaceful may it bring relief ♪

226
00:14:14.312 --> 00:14:16.646
♪ Son of King Adekogbe ♪

227
00:14:16.729 --> 00:14:19.146
[vocalists] ♪ Keep reigning ♪

228
00:14:19.229 --> 00:14:21.312
[singer] ♪ May your time bring relief ♪

229
00:14:21.396 --> 00:14:24.104
♪ Keep reigning ♪

230
00:14:24.187 --> 00:14:26.729
♪ May there be peace and harmony ♪

231
00:14:26.812 --> 00:14:29.354
♪ Keep reigning ♪

232
00:14:29.437 --> 00:14:31.812
♪ May there be prosperity in the land ♪

233
00:14:31.896 --> 00:14:34.021
♪ Keep reigning ♪

234
00:14:34.104 --> 00:14:38.104
[singer adlibs]

235
00:14:56.812 --> 00:14:59.146
♪ Keep reigning ♪

236
00:14:59.229 --> 00:15:01.854
♪ Keep reigning. keep reigning ♪

237
00:15:01.937 --> 00:15:04.354
♪ Keep reigning ♪

238
00:15:04.437 --> 00:15:09.354
-♪ Keep reigning. keep reigning ♪
-[vocalist] ♪ Keep reigning ♪

239
00:15:09.437 --> 00:15:10.521
-♪ Ke-- ♪
-[singing drags abruptly]

240
00:15:10.604 --> 00:15:12.562
[eerie sounds]

241
00:15:22.854 --> 00:15:24.937
[nostalgic music plays]

242
00:15:29.479 --> 00:15:30.771
Priest!

243
00:15:30.854 --> 00:15:32.604
What is it again?

244
00:15:33.187 --> 00:15:34.396
[pensive music plays]

245
00:15:34.479 --> 00:15:35.937
What exactly is the problem now?

246
00:15:38.812 --> 00:15:41.146
You said he who must eat a vulture
must have some pepper.

247
00:15:41.229 --> 00:15:42.312
I have some pepper.

248
00:15:43.854 --> 00:15:47.979
You said he who must eat a vulture
must have palm oil. I have palm oil.

249
00:15:49.687 --> 00:15:53.062
You said he who must eat a vulture
must have lots of salt.

250
00:15:53.854 --> 00:15:55.854
I have lots of salt.

251
00:15:56.687 --> 00:15:59.562
You asked me to close my right eye.
I closed my right eye.

252
00:16:00.937 --> 00:16:04.729
You asked me to fold my left leg.
I folded my left leg.

253
00:16:05.854 --> 00:16:08.479
Yet you left and you came back.

254
00:16:09.562 --> 00:16:11.229
You said vulture cannot be eaten.

255
