00:28:07.687 --> 00:28:10.562
[apprehensive music plays]

531
00:28:15.646 --> 00:28:18.229
[singing continues]

532
00:28:22.271 --> 00:28:27.646
[suspenseful music continues]

533
00:28:37.062 --> 00:28:40.687
Esusu. you have to leave our town.
We no longer want you here.

534
00:28:40.771 --> 00:28:44.437
♪ Esusu. you have to leave our town
We no longer want you here ♪

535
00:28:44.521 --> 00:28:47.771
♪ Esusu. you have to leave our town
We no longer want you here ♪

536
00:28:47.854 --> 00:28:50.396
♪ You have to go! ♪

537
00:28:50.479 --> 00:28:53.771
♪ You have to go! Esusu has to go! ♪

538
00:28:54.354 --> 00:28:57.771
♪ Esusu. you have to leave our town ♪
♪ We no longer want you here ♪

539
00:29:22.062 --> 00:29:26.104
-[growls]
-[chanting halts]

540
00:29:26.187 --> 00:29:28.687
[melancholic music plays]

541
00:29:34.437 --> 00:29:37.396
King Adejuwon. it would have been
better we resolved this on earth

542
00:29:38.021 --> 00:29:40.437
so that it doesn't
become an issue when we get to heaven.

543
00:29:40.521 --> 00:29:42.396
You're not pleased
with me so you sent me away.

544
00:29:43.104 --> 00:29:45.104
you don't like my ways so you expelled me.

545
00:29:46.229 --> 00:29:49.896
Hm! Even though I wish
to stay here longer. [heaves]

546
00:29:49.979 --> 00:29:52.146
but you no longer want me here among you.

547
00:29:52.229 --> 00:29:54.396
[heaves] Ah!

548
00:29:56.146 --> 00:29:57.396
People of Ilara.

549
00:29:58.062 --> 00:30:00.229
just because I have
no relatives in this town.

550
00:30:00.312 --> 00:30:02.271
[crying] that's why you all hate me.

551
00:30:02.354 --> 00:30:04.479
Ah! [panting]

552
00:30:04.562 --> 00:30:05.771
But when we meet again.

553
00:30:05.854 --> 00:30:08.021
[panting] there will be repercussions.

554
00:30:08.104 --> 00:30:10.854
Esusu departs! [supernatural screaming]

555
00:30:11.354 --> 00:30:14.854
[crowd screaming]

556
00:30:15.604 --> 00:30:21.104
-[tense music plays]
-[Esusu screaming] Ah!

557
00:30:26.646 --> 00:30:30.729
[Esusu continues screaming]

558
00:30:41.312 --> 00:30:44.146
-That was how your forefathers used words.
-[sad music plays]

559
00:30:44.229 --> 00:30:45.687
to curse Esusu.

560
00:30:45.771 --> 00:30:49.396
before he became a deity
worshipped with filth.

561
00:30:49.479 --> 00:30:51.312
It's the anger from that time

562
00:30:52.187 --> 00:30:55.646
that made you see what you
told me about when you were called.

563
00:30:57.146 --> 00:30:58.396
Urgh!

564
00:31:01.854 --> 00:31:04.354
What is it? [sighs]

565
00:31:06.521 --> 00:31:09.729
Why do issues
from the past keep affecting me? [huffs]

566
00:31:11.229 --> 00:31:14.604
Why should I be the one
to bear my forefather's burdens?

567
00:31:15.229 --> 00:31:17.146
The sins of your forefathers

568
00:31:17.229 --> 00:31:19.187
must be suffered by their descendants.

569
00:31:19.687 --> 00:31:23.104
You are aware that issues like this
is passed on to generations.

570
00:31:23.187 --> 00:31:26.187
Priest. [huffs]

571
00:31:26.271 --> 00:31:29.437
please what is it? [inhales]

572
00:31:29.521 --> 00:31:32.687
That my my forefathers
did to offend the almighty father.

573
00:31:33.271 --> 00:31:36.229
Huh?! [pants] Priest. help me.

574
00:31:36.312 --> 00:31:37.521
Have mercy on me.

575
00:31:39.104 --> 00:31:40.979
Take a look at me. I'm still young.

576
00:31:41.062 --> 00:31:42.646
Please help me. what can we do?

577
00:31:44.479 --> 00:31:45.896
Your Highness.

578
00:31:46.521 --> 00:31:48.687
you have to get ready. be prepared

579
00:31:50.396 --> 00:31:51.896
to battle with Esusu.

580
00:31:51.979 --> 00:31:53.146
[tense music plays]

581
00:31:53.229 --> 00:31:55.437
You have to expel him out of town.

582
00:31:57.354 --> 00:32:00.021
-I should fight Esusu?
-Yes.

583
00:32:00.604 --> 00:32:01.437
Ah!

584
00:32:05.396 --> 00:32:07.937
Ah. What if I go

585
00:32:08.729 --> 00:32:10.312
and don't come back alive?

586
00:32:11.479 --> 00:32:14.937
It means that your name shall never erase

587
00:32:16.021 --> 00:32:17.812
from the history of Ilara.

588
00:32:20.979 --> 00:32:24.396
[man] ♪ I hail the child
Of the palm tree ♪

589
00:32:24.479 --> 00:32:26.437
-[group] ♪ Hail ♪
-[jingling]

590
00:32:26.521 --> 00:32:28.979
♪ The axe that cuts evil down ♪

591
00:32:29.062 --> 00:32:29.979
Hail…

592
00:32:31.396 --> 00:32:34.521
♪That which the initiates
use to fight evil ♪

593
00:32:34.604 --> 00:32:36.396
♪ Hail ♪

594
00:32:36.479 --> 00:32:39.604
-♪ That's what the gods of Oduru used ♪
-[flute music plays]

595
00:32:39.687 --> 00:32:40.521
♪ Hail ♪

596
00:32:41.521 --> 00:32:45.854
-♪ The gods said I should not relent ♪
-♪ Hail ♪

597
00:32:45.937 --> 00:32:49.021
-♪ No matter how dark it gets ♪
-♪ Hail ♪

598
00:32:50.354 --> 00:32:53.771
♪ We have to keep
Pushing on and on and on ♪

599
00:32:53.854 --> 00:32:58.937
[all] ♪ We have to keep
pushing on and on and on ♪

600
00:33:00.812 --> 00:33:03.771
-[Priest] ♪ On and on and on ♪
-[all after every chant line] ♪ Hail… ♪

601
00:33:04.729 --> 00:33:07.354
-♪ The child keeps pushing ♪
-♪ Hail ♪

602
00:33:08.854 --> 00:33:11.604
-♪ The rain keeps pouring ♪
-[all] ♪ Hail… ♪

603
00:33:12.271 --> 00:33:15.104
♪ A divination was given in the past ♪

604
00:33:16.271 --> 00:33:18.562
♪ The divination
For performing some rituals ♪

605
00:33:19.562 --> 00:33:23.437
♪ We have to keep
Pushing on and on and on ♪

606
00:33:23.521 --> 00:33:28.354
[all] ♪ We have to keep
pushing on and on and on ♪

607
00:33:31.354 --> 00:33:37.854
[chant continues repititively]

608
00:33:44.979 --> 00:33:48.854
-[indistinct incantations]
-[flute music crescendos]

609
00:33:50.979 --> 00:33:52.562
[grunts]

610
00:33:57.271 --> 00:33:58.896
Brave hearted man.

611
00:33:58.979 --> 00:34:00.354
Brave hearted man.

612
00:34:01.229 --> 00:34:02.646
Giant strides!

613
00:34:04.187 --> 00:34:05.687
Call him a lion. put the mark on him.

614
00:34:05.771 --> 00:34:08.146
[repeatedly] Yes!

615
00:34:10.187 --> 00:34:11.937
[flute music crescendos]

616
00:34:14.396 --> 00:34:15.562
Great!

617
00:34:15.646 --> 00:34:17.687
[chants] You are a great man!
Giant strides!

618
00:34:17.771 --> 00:34:20.729
An herbalist doesn't behave impulsively.

619
00:34:20.812 --> 00:34:23.937
-A person acting alone cannot be impulsive
-[man] Yes.

620
00:34:24.021 --> 00:34:26.771
-One cannot be rash because he's angry.
-Yes.

621
00:34:26.854 --> 00:34:29.146
You can't just destroy things
because you are annoyed.

622
00:34:29.229 --> 00:34:32.312
You can't be annoyed
with the swallow and offend the Creator.

623
00:34:32.854 --> 00:34:35.771
An elephant always
gets away with whatever it does.

624
00:34:35.854 --> 00:34:38.104
A buffalo gets away with whatever it does.

625
00:34:38.187 --> 00:34:40.104
-[male voice] Yes.
-When a masquerade commits…

626
00:34:40.187 --> 00:34:44.687
[Queens] ♪ As you go may you return ♪

627
00:34:44.771 --> 00:34:46.937
♪ May you return safely ♪

628
00:34:47.021 --> 00:34:49.271
♪ To your people ♪

629
00:34:49.354 --> 00:34:53.479
♪ As a dog owner walks
He pulls his dog along ♪

630
00:34:53.562 --> 00:34:54.479
[Priest] Go ahead!

631
00:34:54.562 --> 00:34:57.229
[all] He is now an initiate.

632
00:34:57.312 --> 00:34:58.729
Go ahead!

633
00:34:58.812 --> 00:35:01.854
-[all] He's now an initiate.
-[Priest] You are now an initiate.

634
00:35:01.937 --> 00:35:05.062
-[all] He's now an initiate
-[Priest] Go ahead! You're now an initiate

635
00:35:05.146 --> 00:35:07.396
-[all] He's now an initiate
-[Priest] Go ahead…

636
00:35:11.187 --> 00:35:15.062
-He's now an initiate
-You are now an initiate.

637
00:35:15.146 --> 00:35:19.687
[Queens] ♪ As a dog owner walk.
He pulls his dog along ♪

638
00:35:20.854 --> 00:35:23.312
-♪ He's now an initiate ♪
-[queens continue singing]

639
00:35:25.062 --> 00:35:27.312
[flute music swells]

640
00:35:28.937 --> 00:35:31.187
[suspenseful music plays]

641
00:35:31.271 --> 00:35:33.771
♪ He's now an initiate♪

642
00:35:33.854 --> 00:35:37.854
Esusu! [pants]

643
00:35:39.604 --> 00:35:43.312
Esusu! [pants]

644
00:35:43.396 --> 00:35:45.979
Esusu! [pants]

645
00:35:46.062 --> 00:35:47.437
I call upon you.

646
00:35:47.521 --> 00:35:50.146
and you must hear my call.

647
00:35:51.312 --> 00:35:53.687
I have come to expel you today.

648
00:35:53.771 --> 00:35:54.687
[jingling]

649
00:35:54.771 --> 00:35:57.562
Today! You must leave Ilara town!

650
00:35:57.646 --> 00:35:59.229
[jingling]

651
00:35:59.312 --> 00:36:02.354
Esusu! You are banished!

652
00:36:02.437 --> 00:36:05.312
-[jingling]
-Esusu now get up!

653
00:36:05.396 --> 00:36:10.646
[Esusu roars]

654
00:36:15.146 --> 00:36:17.729
[Esusu roars] No!

655
00:36:18.437 --> 00:36:24.854
No! No!

656
00:36:26.396 --> 00:36:30.146
[indistinct incantations]

657
00:36:30.229 --> 00:36:34.979
[Esusu] This is war. [growls]

658
00:36:35.062 --> 00:36:38.187
-[panicked indistinct chatters]
-[Esusu growls]

659
00:36:38.271 --> 00:36:39.187
-[Amaka yelps]
-You lie!

660
00:36:39.271 --> 00:36:40.896
-[man in the crowd] Ah!
-That can't be!

661
00:36:40.979 --> 00:36:41.979
The archer uses

662
00:36:42.062 --> 00:36:46.021
the bow to shoot the arrow away.
while the bowstring is in the arch!

663
00:36:46.104 --> 00:36:47.479
I command you!

664
00:36:48.104 --> 00:36:51.187
When an axe cuts the tree
in the bush. its strikes hard!

665
00:36:51.271 --> 00:36:53.187
Hard!

666
00:36:54.479 --> 00:36:55.854
I hail my fathers.

667
00:36:56.437 --> 00:36:58.271
I hail the ones before me!

668
00:36:58.354 --> 00:36:59.562
Esusu!

669
00:36:59.646 --> 00:37:01.271
You've set eyes on me today.

670
00:37:01.812 --> 00:37:02.854
you've seen death.

671
00:37:02.937 --> 00:37:04.354
I cast you out!

672
00:37:04.437 --> 00:37:07.146
[growls]

673
00:37:07.229 --> 00:37:11.062
-[Esusu] Impossible. [groans]
-[growls]

674
00:37:11.604 --> 00:37:13.104
-You can't conquer me.
-[Adedunjoye yelps]

675
00:37:13.187 --> 00:37:14.979
-You can't send me away!
-[yelps]

676
00:37:15.062 --> 00:37:16.771
-Ilara you're in trouble!
-Ah!

677
00:37:16.854 --> 00:37:18.687
-[Esusu] You the king will equally suffer.
-[yelps]

678
00:37:18.771 --> 00:37:20.062
-You sent me here.
-[groans]

679
00:37:20.146 --> 00:37:21.104
I'm not leaving.

680
00:37:21.187 --> 00:37:23.479
I'm prepared to receive
a visitor at my place.

681
00:37:23.562 --> 00:37:25.021
[Esusu] Oh. ground I beseech you!

682
00:37:25.104 --> 00:37:26.187
Do not betray me!

683
00:37:26.271 --> 00:37:31.104
-Oh ground open up and swallow up!
-[Adedunjoye yelps]

684
00:37:31.812 --> 00:37:32.854
[sad music plays]

685
00:37:33.354 --> 00:37:36.104
[indistinct]

686
00:37:36.187 --> 00:37:37.771
[a Queen yelps]

687
00:37:38.896 --> 00:37:41.562
[music shifts to quizzical]

688
00:37:43.812 --> 00:37:48.604
[Esusu howling]

689
00:37:50.062 --> 00:37:51.812
[supernatural noises]

690
00:37:53.021 --> 00:37:54.271
[exclaims] Oh!

691
00:37:54.354 --> 00:37:56.521
The one who treads
carefully in an unknown place!

692
00:37:57.062 --> 00:37:59.187
Purity will always overcome evil!

693
00:37:59.771 --> 00:38:01.729
The one who dwells in the heavens.

694
00:38:02.312 --> 00:38:03.729
will come through for Orunmila!

695
00:38:04.354 --> 00:38:08.479
[both groan]

696
00:38:09.062 --> 00:38:14.646
-[yelps]
-[Esusu growls]

697
00:38:14.729 --> 00:38:16.312
[Esusu heaving]
I went as far as the heavens

698
00:38:16.396 --> 00:38:17.979
to attain powers. [pants]

699
00:38:18.062 --> 00:38:21.479
I went as far
as the seas to get fortified.

700
00:38:21.562 --> 00:38:25.437
[panting] May all I do.
not have any repercussions.

701
00:38:25.521 --> 00:38:28.437
Give me the power to overcome
and get away with whatever I do.

702
00:38:28.521 --> 00:38:32.604
[panting] I will not fail
at what I do! I will not fail!

703
00:38:33.479 --> 00:38:35.479
-[Esusu groans]
-[pants]

704
00:38:35.562 --> 00:38:38.562
-[Esusu] Kill him.
-[groans]

705
00:38:38.646 --> 00:38:45.104
-[Esusu growl]
-[growls. pants]

706
00:38:45.187 --> 00:38:49.562
Adekogbe! [panting]

707
00:38:49.646 --> 00:38:51.146
Son of Adarisode.

708
00:38:51.229 --> 00:38:53.812
-[pants]
-have mercy on me! [heaves]

709
00:38:53.896 --> 00:38:55.771
Don't let Esusu kill me.

710
00:38:55.854 --> 00:38:58.437
-[pants]
-I'm fighting for Ilara. [pants]

711
00:38:58.521 --> 00:38:59.896
Ilara is the house you built.

712
00:39:00.604 --> 00:39:02.062
Adekogbe don't allow it to crumble.

713
00:39:03.271 --> 00:39:06.271
[yells] Adekogbe!

714
00:39:08.062 --> 00:39:10.812
[Esusu pants]

715
00:39:10.896 --> 00:39:13.771
[suspenseful music plays]

716
00:39:13.854 --> 00:39:19.604
[Adedunjoye pants]

717
00:39:22.979 --> 00:39:25.021
[Esusus groans]

718
00:39:25.104 --> 00:39:26.937
No one can banish me from my own abode.

719
00:39:27.021 --> 00:39:29.479
I told you not to offend me but you did.

720
00:39:30.104 --> 00:39:33.062
[panting] Ilara people.
you can't take me out so easily.

721
00:39:33.146 --> 00:39:35.604
I am wickedness! [roars]

722
00:39:38.646 --> 00:39:40.396
[pensive music plays]

723
00:39:40.979 --> 00:39:42.771
[Priest] He's a star that shines.

724
00:39:43.687 --> 00:39:46.854
[Queens cheer]

725
00:39:50.021 --> 00:39:52.229
-Great king!
-[elders hailing]

726
00:39:52.312 --> 00:39:54.437
-[crowd cheers]
-[Amaka cheers]

727
00:39:54.521 --> 00:39:55.812
[man] Ah!

728
00:39:59.937 --> 00:40:04.729
[all] Your Highness.

729
00:40:10.687 --> 00:40:12.562
[Priest] Ehh!

730
00:40:17.729 --> 00:40:23.771
[soft music playing]

